                <div type="general">
                    <p xml:space="preserve">Al-Shirqat is an Iraqi Sunni Arab town located on the Tigris some 
               100 km south of Mosul. The ruins of the famous ancient Assyrian city of Assur are situated near it.</p>
                </div>
                <div type="researchHistory">
                    <p xml:space="preserve">Hitherto the only description of the dialect of Al-Shirqat has 
               been <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:ESQZAJRJ">Salonen (1980)</rs>. It consists of two sections: 
               a collection of 17 texts, and a grammatical sketch. The grammar discusses phonology and 
               morphology, the latter divided into subchapters on pronouns, verbs, particles, etc. The 
               morphology chapter also includes a comparison of the morphology of the dialect of Al-Shirqat with that of Mosul.</p>
                </div>
